cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the representation of graphs using orthogonal polygons and vertical/horizontal visibilities, which are common topics in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents polynomial time algorithms for testing the existence of an OPVR and computing one of minimum vertex complexity. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses the relationship between the existence and vertex complexity of an OPVR and the number of crossings per edge and connectivity of the graph, which are discrete mathematical concepts. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is possible as the paper mentions the concept of connectivity, which is also relevant in game theory. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the representation of graphs using visual elements such as polygons and visibilities.
